configuration for terminal including vim, screen, and tmux settings

to install, from your home directory, run the following command:
	curl -SsL https://raw.github.com/smenzer/terminal/master/setup | bash [-s machine [target]]
	
	machine is the name that will be used to create a unique bash profile.  it will default to the machine hostname if not specified
	target is the directory to install to.  it will default to ~/ if you don't specify it
